  <static seed="13" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/PolynomialMultiplication/PolynomialMultiplication15.pg">
    <statement><p>Multiply the polynomials.</p>
<p><m>{-7y^{2}}\left({7y^{2}+5y}\right)=</m><fillin characters="16" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-49y^{4}-35y^{3}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We multiply the monomial by each term in the binomial, using 
the properties of exponents to help us</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
              {-7y^{2}}({7y^{2}+5y})\amp ={-49y^{4}-35y^{3}}
      \end{aligned}</m></p>
</solution>
